7) 
\b\fs28 Aliasing
\b0\fs24 \
\
It occurs when the signal is not sampled fast enough for construction of an accurate waveform record. So, the oscilloscope displays whether a waveform with a frequency lower than the actual waveform or an unstable waveform.\
\
\ul Solution\ulnone : The signal must be sampled more than twice as fast as \ul the highest frequency component\ulnone  of the signal (
\b Nyquist Theorem
\b0 ).\
